Remarks were made by Vice President Mike Pence at the Las Vegas Unity Prayer Walk in response to the mass shooting that occurred in Las Vegas on October 1, 2017. Pence expressed his condolences to the families of the victims and praised the heroic actions of first responders and everyday Americans who risked their lives to help others. He emphasized the unity and resilience of the American people in the face of evil and called for prayers for healing and unity. Pence concluded by asking for God's blessings on America and its citizens.